  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f125d2b8a81022987559f0903a77ab",
        "content": [
          "1) Data Scope and Join Rules\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Current status queries:\r\n",
          "  Use `gold_de_aml_snapshot_customer_enriched_v` and filter `DateID = Yesterday` (YYYYMMDD integer) use as default If no specific date is provided.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Historical queries:\r\n",
          "  Use `gold_de_aml_snapshot_customer_enriched_v` with explicit `DateID` filter(s) (YYYYMMDD integer).\r\n",
          "  Do not use MAX(DateID) as a substitute for a requested date/range.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Active KYC Profiles: \r\n",
          "  Always filter kyc_for_compliance_v by Is_Current = 1 unless history is specifically requested.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Join keys:\r\n",
          "  Join by the customer identifier concept.\r\n",
          "  For joins to `bi_output_vg_mimo_slim`, `bi_output_vg_aum_slim`, 'cfd_statusinfo_v', and `bi_output_vg_revenue_slim`, use `RealCID` (not `CID`).\r\n",
          "  Keep date grain aligned by joining on `DateID` when date-level metrics are required.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Mandatory Clarifications (Ask Before Executing):\r\n",
          "  Verification Level: Unless specified otherwise, clarify the required level. \r\n",
          "  Status Filtering: If not mentioned, ask if \"Blocked\" or \"Restricted\" customers should be excluded.\r\n",
          "  Default logic: Usually, PlayerStatus \"Blocked\" and \"Blocked Upon Request\"- BUR should be excluded.\r\n",
          "  New Customers: If the user asks for \"New Customers,\" clarify if they mean New Registrations or New FTDs.\r\n",
          "  Client Jurisdiction: Clarify with the user Is the requirement KYC Country, Citizenship, or Place of Birth (POB)\r\n",
